column2: TBI on CT (determined by PI)
column5:
The first traumatic head CT of any patient was reviewed in order to determine if there was a TBI on CT. TBI on CT is defined as any of the traumatic findings (1-23) below, except for skull fracture. Skull fractures were not regarded as TBIs unless the fracture was depressed by at least the width of the skull.
 

 Not applicable is marked if no head CT was performed.

column2: Head CT performed in ED
